  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Educate 800 villagers on COVID-19 in Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CDVTA plans to educate 800 elders, women, disabled and people with frail health conditions on the covid-19 outbreak in Cameroon ensuring that information on this pandemic is accessible to locals in 8 poorest villages. The project will train and support 50 local volunteers to sensitize and educate the population on preventive measures while providing protective gear and hand sanitizers to 800 needy persons. Hand washing facilities will be installed in the villages for Covid-19 prevention</narrative>
  </description>
